captions.text:
-Welcome to Cute
Girls Hairstyles

and I am CGH number
three and today I'm
going to get interviewed.

-So last week we asked
fans to submit questions

that they would want CGH
number three to answer

and these are the
questions, some
of the questions we picked.

So shortstopslider
asks, how old are you?
-Nine.

-OK, Gracie Cookie asks,
what grade are you in?
-Fourth grade.

-Orangedazzle is asking, what
is your most favorite thing

about school and what
is your least favorite?

-I like reading and I
don't like spelling.
-Why don't you like spelling?

-Because it's boring
because we have

to write them down in
syllables and mark them.
So yeah, it's boring.

-Just for the record,
she's an excellent speller.

She won her class
spelling bee last year.

OK, so SevenDeckerBus asks,
does your third daughter--
you-- read books?

And if so, what
are your favorites?

-I love to read
books and my favorite
is this series that I'm reading.

The first book is the
"Uglies" and it's really good.

-Well, do you know
the rest of the names
of the books in the series?

-The second one
is the "Pretties,"

the third one is the
"Specials," and the fourth one
is the "Extras."

-BubblyNinjaHiga asks, what
does she want, what do you
want to be when you grow up?
-A dentist or an orthodontist.

-Catinthehat9751 asks,
for your third girl

I'd like to know what
brand of mascara she uses.
-I don't have mascara.
-Those are all natural?
-Yeah.

-Do we ever put mascara
on your eyelashes?
-No.
-Well, for your dance recitals.
-Dance recitals, but that's it.

-So close your and
tip your head down

and let them see
those natural wonders.

Yes, it's all natural
from her daddy.

SilverFeather15 asks, do you
like having your hair done?
-Yeah, it's a lot of fun.

-Let's see, Shooter21Des
asks, do you

do your hair every day
or only for videos?
-Everyday.
-Does mom do it every day?

Do I do it or do
you do it sometimes?

-My mom does it and sometimes
when we're in a hurry

I just like do a braid
or something easy.

-Do you know how to
do some hairstyles?
-Yeah.
-What do you know how to do?

-Um, a braid, a
ponytail, and a fishtail

braid, and I think I might know
how to do the knotted headband.

-Casssiemassie, I hope
I said that right, asks,

what is your absolute
favorite hairstyle?

-The waterfall braid
because I like it

because it's like cool
because it like does a braid

and then drops
down and it's cool.

-Kanfusol asks, do you and your
sisters do each other's hair?

-Sometimes they do my hair and
rarely they let me do theirs.

-Kelsie23rocks asks, do the
teachers and kids at schools

always wonder how your
mom does your hair

and want you your
mom to do their hair?
-Yes, a lot.
-Mm-hmm.

-Every single day I
have a different one

and they always ask how I do
it, how she did it and stuff.

-OK, monkeylove314 asks, can I
please be part of your family?
-If my mom and dad will let you.
-OK, next set of questions.

You get asked this
a lot and I know

you're going to smile
when you hear it.
But why are you so cute?

Please answer this one, is
what ilovemultiples said.

-Um, because my mom is pretty
and my dad is handsome.
-Ooh.
-That was pretty fair.

-OK, tinythea39
said, do you know

that you're a very lucky
girl to have a mom like Mindy
and to have those eyelashes?
I'm jealous of you, LOL.

-Oh, lots of people say that,
so yeah, I did know that.

-Thebubblegumchewer
10 says, what's

the most embarrassing thing
that has ever happened to you?
-Oh, I don't know.
Let's see.
I don't know.

-I remember watching a family
video of you and you were like
18 months old--
-Oh.

---trying to climb
out of your crib.
What happened?

-Um, my mom told me to climb
out of my crib and I fell out.
-And we have it on camera.
-Yeah.
-Yeah.
It's pretty funny.

-SmileyKiley07 wants to
know what sports do you do?

-I do dancing and
tumbling and that's it.
Right?
-Yeah.
What tumbling do you do?

-I can do a power round
off back handspring,

I can do flat back
handsprings, I

can do a standing round
off back handspring,
and I almost have my aerial.

Then I can do the simple
stuff like front walkovers

and back walkovers
and stuff like that.

-Sunshinelollupop asks, how
many videos have you been in?
-Um, a lot, like hundreds.
I don't know how many.

-Who normally
volunteers when mom

asks who wants to
do a hairstyle?
-Me.
-Why?

-Because it's fun and
I like the hairstyles,
seeing how she does them.

-Will you make videos on
YouTube when you're old enough?
-Yeah.
-Yeah?
What kind of videos will you do?

-Um, probably like art or
cooking or something like that.

-MelroseMomf3 asks, do you
like being in a big family?

And do you like having
adopted siblings?

-Yeah, I think being
in a big family.

And having adopted
siblings is a lot of fun

because they just
like toddle around
and they're like so fun, yeah.

-OK, CuteDIYandHairstyles
wants to know,

would you rather be a giant
mouse or a tiny elephant?
-A giant mouse.
-Why?

-Because if you were
a tiny elephant then

you would get squashed
like a bug, so yeah.
-Yes, that might happen.

Areeje Khane asks,
what are your hobbies?

-Um, I do dancing
and tumbling and I--

-What do you like to do though
when you're not doing school
or your after school stuff?
-Oh, OK.
I wasn't sure what hobbies were.
OK.
-Yeah.

-I like to ride my bike
and jump on the tramp
and do stuff like that.

-OK, MaybeeBabee14 asks, where
is your favorite place to be?
-Home or school.

-You don't like a
trip or camping?
You'd rather be home?
-Depends on what we're doing.
-Well, let's do this.
What's your favorite movie?
-"Tangled," that's cute.

-Aaliyah Fassolis-- I hope
I said that right-- asks,

if a giant pear came into your
room and started talking to you
what would you do?
-I would eat it.
-You'd eat it?

-Yes, I would eat
the talking pear.

-That might be a lot of
pear if it was a giant pear.

Fudgefjs asks, does anyone
ever recognize you at school
from YouTube?
-Yeah.

Even if I've never seen
them before they're

like, hey aren't you that girl
from Cute Girls Hairstyles?
I'm like, yeah.
-Do you share a room?
-No.
I don't.
-Do the twins share a room?
-Yes.

-Yeah, so you got lucky
and got your own room, huh.
-Mm-hmm.

Winxclub4ever1000 wants to
know if you like anyone.
-No, I don't like anybody.
-No crushes.
-Nope.
-Do people have crushes on you?
-Yes.
-How many?
One, ten, twenty?
-I don't know, a lot.
-A lot.

How do you know they
have a crush on you?

-I play four square at recess
and they either get you out
or they are really nice to you.

And yeah, so that's
how you know.

-OK, so let's see
the next question.

Sportlover16764 asks, do you
prefer candy or chocolate?
-Chocolate.

-Yeah, she's a girl
after my own heart.

What's your very
favorite chocolate?
-Ooh, dark chocolate.
I like dark chocolate Doves.

-Doves, yeah those
are my favorite too.

-OK, NancyBeiber
wants to know who

do you prefer Justin
Bieber or One Direction?
-One Direction.

-Rachelleavitt, who is your
daughter's favorite Disney
character and why?

-Either Merida or
Rapunzel from "Tangled."

Ella hadd asks, do
you like Nutella?

-Oh, is that the peanut
butter and jelly mixed
together thingy mabobber?
-No.
-Wait, what is that?

-Nutella is that hazelnut
chocolate spread.
-Oh, yeah.

That thing where you
put it on your bread.
-Yeah.
-I don't like that.

-OK, cheerleaderaam95 asks,
what's your favorite food?
-Baked potatoes and steak.

-Zahratheawesome-- holy smokes,
I hope I said that right--

says, if you had one day to
buy anything and only one thing

in the world what
would it be and why?

-My cousin, she's 17,
she has brain cancer

has probably I think it's
less than a 7% chance
to live for a year.

And I would buy all the
doctors and medicines

that she needed to
survive, that's it.
-That's really sweet, sweetie.

OK, I think that's
all of our questions.

Do you have anything else you
want to just tell them for fun?
-Love you, see you later.
-See ya.
-Bye.
